-- PRESS DIGEST - Bulgaria - Oct 10
-- 
-- Fri Oct 10, 2014 02:58AM EDT
-- None



SOFIA, Oct 10 (Reuters) - These are some of the main stories in Bulgarian newspapers on Friday. Reuters has not verified these stories and does not vouch for their accuracy.

-- Bulgaria's export to EU countries in the first seven months of the year was 15.2 billion levs (9.87 billion US dollar), a 3.6 percent increase on an annual basis, the statistics office data showed. The import from EU countries in Jan-July was 17.7 billion levs, a 2.3 percent increase on an annual basis (Trud, Standart, Monitor).  -- Interim Defence Minister Velizar Shalamanov deserves a court trial, nationalist Attack party leader Volen Siderov said, blaming the minister of involving Bulgaria in war. Siderov, whose party opened their election campaign in Moscow, made his comments following a controversy with Russia's deputy Prime Minister Dmitry Rogozin Twitter comment over the potential purchase of second-hand warplanes, built in the West and the following response of Bulgaria's caretaker Foreign Minister Daniel Mitov.